Clusters matched to a well-reconstructed ID track originating from a vertex found in the beam interaction region are classified as electrons. If the matched track is consistent with originating from a photon conversion and if in addition a conversion vertex is reconstructed, the corresponding candidates are considered as converted photons. They are classified as single-track or double-track conversions depending on the number of assigned electron-tracks. Clusters without matching tracks are classified as unconverted photons [5]. The electron cluster is then rebuilt using an area of calorimeter cells corresponding to 3 ×\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
