A set of corrections are implemented to account for response variations not included in the simulation in specific detector regions (step 4), e.g. non-optimal HV regions, geometric effects such as the inter-module widening (IMW) or biases associated with the LAr calorimeter electronic calibration. These corrections are discussed in Sect. 6, where the stability of the calorimeter response as a function of ϕ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
