				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$1.8<|\eta |<2.3$$\end{document}, with an uncertainty rising from 1 to 5 % in this region. Since in this region most high-ET\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$E_{\mathrm {T}}$$\end{document} EM showers have their highest energy cell in L1 recorded in MG, this additional uncertainty is accounted for when applying the muon-based calibration to electrons or photons.

